stateDiagram-v2
  [*] --> created: createRuntimeSupervisor

  created --> verifying: bootstrap → createPlatform
  verifying --> starting: startupVerifier passes
  verifying --> failed: startupVerifier fails (ABORT)
  starting --> ready: platform.start() + sampleHealth

  ready --> degraded: sampleHealth → overall=false
  degraded --> ready: sampleHealth → overall=true

  ready --> shutting_down: runtime.shutdown()
  degraded --> shutting_down: runtime.shutdown()
  shutting_down --> stopped: Lifecycle stop + verify
  shutting_down --> failed: shutdown timeout (not forced)

  ready --> restarting: runtime.restart()
  degraded --> restarting: runtime.restart()
  restarting --> ready: verify → shutdown → rebuild → start → verify
  restarting --> failed: any restart step fails

  failed --> [*]
  stopped --> [*]

  note right of shutting_down
    shutdown() delegates to the Lifecycle Kernel (ADR-040):
    kernels stop in reverse dependency order. The Shutdown
    Manager adds timeout + force policy and verifies that no
    lifecycle components remain started.
  end note

  note right of restarting
    restart() reuses the SAME assemble() path bootstrap uses
    (create → verify → start), so composition logic is never
    duplicated. The supervisor persists and counts restarts.
  end note
